{"questionId":"27664","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Consider the homogeneous differential equation&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mi>y</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>, where&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>≠</mo><mn>0</mn></math>.</p>\n<p>It is given that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math> when <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>By using the substitution <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>v</mi><mi>x</mi></math>, solve the differential equation. Give your answer in the form <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mi>f</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mi>y</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>let&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>v</mi><mi>x</mi></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi>v</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>x</mi><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>v</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(</strong><strong>A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><mi>v</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>x</mi><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>v</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>v</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mrow><mi>v</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M</strong><strong>1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><mi>x</mi><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>v</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow><mi>v</mi></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(</strong><strong>A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><mo>∫</mo><mi>v</mi><mo>d</mo><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mo>∫</mo><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi></mfrac><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>M</strong><strong>1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>v</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mi>ln</mi><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> Condone the absence of the modulus sign up to this point.</p>\n<p><br><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mrow><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mi>ln</mi><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to substitute <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math> into their integrated expression to find <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>M</strong><strong>1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mi>ln</mi><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mn>1</mn></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi><mo>⇒</mo><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mrow><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mi>ln</mi><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mi>ln</mi><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>ln</mi><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[8 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"27664","referenceCode":"22N.1.AHL.TZ0.9a","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-appr